 :tx/rationale "ADR-024 OBSERVATION 10: IMPEDANCE MATCHING — TWO ATTENTION MECHANISMS. The LLM is ALSO a transformer. When braid projects into the LLM's context window, two attention mechanisms interact: braid's A(t) (which information to project) and the LLM's self-attention (which tokens to attend to). The OPTIMAL output is one where these are RESONANT — braid presents tokens the LLM's attention will naturally weight highly. This is impedance matching for intelligence. In electronics: max power when source Z = load Z. In information theory: max transfer when encoding matches channel. The LLM's attention pattern IS the channel. Braid's encoding should match it. The channel characteristics are LEARNABLE through the observe-calibrate loop."
